{"questionId":"33230963","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The random variable <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> is defined as the number of red buttons selected by Francine.</p>\n<p>The following table shows the probability distribution of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/299e38c6b0959c8b9b4dcd9c371bbfd4efc762c8.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33230963","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.9d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of a and the value of b.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}